AgentLogFacility.name: AgentLogFacility
AgentLogFacility.description: Facility code used in determining the SysLog Priority value.

AgentLogSeverity.name: AgentLogSeverity
AgentLogSeverity.description: Severity code used in determining the SysLog Priority value.

logging.name: logging
logging.contactinfo: Customer Support Postal: Quanta Computer Inc. 4, Wen Ming 1 St., Kuei Shan Hsiang, Tao Yuan Shien, Taiwan, R.O.C. Tel: +886 3 328 0050 E-Mail: strong.chen@quantatw.com
logging.description: This MIB provides objects to configure and display events logged on this system.

agentLogInMemoryAdminStatus.name: agentLogInMemoryAdminStatus
agentLogInMemoryAdminStatus.description: Administratively enable/disable the In Memory log.

agentLogInMemoryBehavior.name: agentLogInMemoryBehavior
agentLogInMemoryBehavior.description: Configures the behavior of the In Memory Log when it becomes full. A value of wrap(1) will cause the oldest log message to be removed, making room for the new message. A value of stop-on-full(2) will prevent any further logging.

agentLogSyslogAdminStatus.name: agentLogSyslogAdminStatus
agentLogSyslogAdminStatus.description: For Enabling and Disabling logging to configured syslog hosts. Setting this to disable stops logging to all syslog hosts.

agentLogSyslogLocalPort.name: agentLogSyslogLocalPort
agentLogSyslogLocalPort.description: This is the port on the local host from which syslog messages are sent.

agentLogSyslogMaxHosts.name: agentLogSyslogMaxHosts
agentLogSyslogMaxHosts.description: Maximum number of hosts that can be configured for logging syslog messages.

agentLogCliCommandsAdminStatus.name: agentLogCliCommandsAdminStatus
agentLogCliCommandsAdminStatus.description: Administratively enable/disable the logging of the CLI Commands

agentLogSyslogHostTable.name: agentLogSyslogHostTable
agentLogSyslogHostTable.description: Syslog host table containing syslog host entries.

agentLogHostTableIndex.name: agentLogHostTableIndex
agentLogHostTableIndex.description: Index to syslog host entry in syslog host table.

agentLogHostTableSeverityFilter.name: agentLogHostTableSeverityFilter
agentLogHostTableSeverityFilter.description: Configures the minimum severity that will be stored in the In Memory log.

agentLogSyslogSourceInterface.name: agentLogSyslogSourceInterface
agentLogSyslogSourceInterface.description: A source-interface selection on an Interface Index (like vlan based routing interface, port based routing interface, loopback interface, tunnel interface). A non-zero value indicates ifIndex for the corresponding interface entry in the ifTable is selected. A zero value indicates the source-interface un-selection.

agentLogSyslogFacility.name: agentLogSyslogFacility
agentLogSyslogFacility.description: This is the facility which is sent in syslog messages.

agentLogMessagesReceived.name: agentLogMessagesReceived
agentLogMessagesReceived.description: The number of messages received by the log process. This includes messages that are dropped or ignored.

agentLogMessagesDropped.name: agentLogMessagesDropped
agentLogMessagesDropped.description: The number of messages that could not be processed due to error or lack of resources.

agentLogSyslogMessagesRelayed.name: agentLogSyslogMessagesRelayed
agentLogSyslogMessagesRelayed.description: The number of messages forwarded by the syslog function to a syslog host. Messages forwarded to multiple hosts are counted once for each host.

agentLogSyslogMessagesIgnored.name: agentLogSyslogMessagesIgnored
agentLogSyslogMessagesIgnored.description: The number of messages that were not processed by the syslog process because the component name or the priority level did not match any specification.

agentLogMessageReceivedTime.name: agentLogMessageReceivedTime
agentLogMessageReceivedTime.description: The local time when a message was last received by the log subsystem specified as the number of non-leap seconds since 00:00:00 UTC on January 1 1970.

agentLogSyslogMessageDeliveredTime.name: agentLogSyslogMessageDeliveredTime
agentLogSyslogMessageDeliveredTime.description: The local time when a message was last delivered to a syslog host specified as the number of non-leap seconds since 00:00:00 UTC on January 1 1970.

agentLogEmailAdminStatus.name: agentLogEmailAdminStatus
agentLogEmailAdminStatus.description: For Enabling and Disabling email alerts to SMTP server. Setting this to disable stops emailing to SMTP servers.

agentLogEmailfromAddr.name: agentLogEmailfromAddr
agentLogEmailfromAddr.description: Sender Email Address. Maximum length is 255

agentLogEmaillogDuration.name: agentLogEmaillogDuration
agentLogEmaillogDuration.description: This duration in minutes determines how frequently the non critical messages are sent to the SMTP server.

agentLogEmailUrgentSeverity.name: agentLogEmailUrgentSeverity
agentLogEmailUrgentSeverity.description: This is the severity level for the critical log messages

agentLogEmailNonUrgentSeverity.name: agentLogEmailNonUrgentSeverity
agentLogEmailNonUrgentSeverity.description: This is the severity level for the non critical log messages.

agentLogEmailUrgentAdminStatus.name: agentLogEmailUrgentAdminStatus
agentLogEmailUrgentAdminStatus.description: For Enabling and Disabling email urgent alerts to SMTP server. Setting this to disable stops urgent emailing to SMTP servers.

agentLogEmailNonUrgentAdminStatus.name: agentLogEmailNonUrgentAdminStatus
agentLogEmailNonUrgentAdminStatus.description: For Enabling and Disabling email non-urgent alerts to SMTP server. Setting this to disable stops non-urgent emailing to SMTP servers.

agentLogEmailTrapsSeverity.name: agentLogEmailTrapsSeverity
agentLogEmailTrapsSeverity.description: This is the severity level for Trap messages.

agentLogEmailToAddrTable.name: agentLogEmailToAddrTable
agentLogEmailToAddrTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the destination email address and the message type.

agentLogEmailToAddrEntry.name: agentLogEmailToAddrEntry
agentLogEmailToAddrEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the agentLogEmailtoAddrTable. This entry shows what kind of messages go to the given destination email addresses.

agentLogEmailToAddr.name: agentLogEmailToAddr
agentLogEmailToAddr.description: Recipient Email Address. Maximum length is 255

agentLogEmailToAddrEntryStatus.name: agentLogEmailToAddrEntryStatus
agentLogEmailToAddrEntryStatus.description: This is to create or delete the entry

agentLogEmailSubjectTable.name: agentLogEmailSubjectTable
agentLogEmailSubjectTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the subject of the email and the message type.

agentLogEmailSubjectEntry.name: agentLogEmailSubjectEntry
agentLogEmailSubjectEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the agentLogEmailtoAddrTable. This entry shows what kind of subject to be used for the given message type.

agentLogEmailSubject.name: agentLogEmailSubject
agentLogEmailSubject.description: Email Subject. Maximum length is 255. When this object is set to empty-string, it resets to factory default string.

agentLogEmailSubjectEntryStatus.name: agentLogEmailSubjectEntryStatus
agentLogEmailSubjectEntryStatus.description: This is to create or delete the entry

agentLogEmailMailServerTable.name: agentLogEmailMailServerTable
agentLogEmailMailServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mail servers

agentLogEmailMailServerEntry.name: agentLogEmailMailServerEntry
agentLogEmailMailServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the agentLogEmailMailServerTable. This entry shows the conmfiguration for mail server.

agentLogEmailSmtpPort.name: agentLogEmailSmtpPort
agentLogEmailSmtpPort.description: SMTP Port number. When this object is set to 0, it resets to factory default port number.

agentLogEmailSecurity.name: agentLogEmailSecurity
agentLogEmailSecurity.description: This is the authentication mechanism that should be used. Well known port for none security is 25, sslv3/tlsv1 is 465, and starttls is 587 or 25.

agentLogEmailloginID.name: agentLogEmailloginID
agentLogEmailloginID.description: This user id is used while the switch/router is being authenticated by the SMTP server.The user ID should be minimum of 1 charcter to maximum of 32 characters.

agentLogEmailPassword.name: agentLogEmailPassword
agentLogEmailPassword.description: This password is used while the switch/router is being authenticated by the SMTP server.The password should be minimum of 1 character to maximum of 32 characters.

agentLogEmailEntryStatus.name: agentLogEmailEntryStatus
agentLogEmailEntryStatus.description: This is to create or delete the entry

agentLogEmailStatsemailsSentCount.name: agentLogEmailStatsemailsSentCount
agentLogEmailStatsemailsSentCount.description: This is the count to show the no of emails sent so far.

agentLogEmailStatsemailsFailureCount.name: agentLogEmailStatsemailsFailureCount
agentLogEmailStatsemailsFailureCount.description: This is the count to show the no of emails failures happened so far...

agentLogEmailStatsTimeSinceLastEmailSent.name: agentLogEmailStatsTimeSinceLastEmailSent
agentLogEmailStatsTimeSinceLastEmailSent.description: This is the number of seconds since the last email was sent.

agentLogEmailStatsClear.name: agentLogEmailStatsClear
agentLogEmailStatsClear.description: This is to clear the email alert stats.

agentLogInMemoryLogCount.name: agentLogInMemoryLogCount
agentLogInMemoryLogCount.description: The count of valid entries in the in-memory log.

agentLogInMemoryTable.name: agentLogInMemoryTable
agentLogInMemoryTable.description: The in-memory log table containing sequence of in-memory log entries.

agentLogInMemoryEntry.name: agentLogInMemoryEntry
agentLogInMemoryEntry.description: An individual message entry in in-memory log table.

agentLogInMemoryMsgIndex.name: agentLogInMemoryMsgIndex
agentLogInMemoryMsgIndex.description: The index to message entry in the in-memory log table.

agentLogInMemoryMsgText.name: agentLogInMemoryMsgText
agentLogInMemoryMsgText.description: Message text info for inmemory logged messages.

agentLogEmailSendFailed.name: agentLogEmailSendFailed
agentLogEmailSendFailed.description: When ever a mail sending to the SMTP server is failed, this trap is sent with a count of how many times the connection to the SMTP server is failed so far.
